        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 22 at 6:30AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 625 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of heavy snow
showers extending from near Neihart to 25 miles southwest of Dillon.
Movement was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...This line of snow will produce brief periods of heavy snow,
visibility below one half mile and wind gusts around 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar and observation indicated.

IMPACT...Reduced visibility and snow covered roads will create
difficult travel conditions this morning.

Locations impacted include...
Three Forks, Big Sky, Bozeman, West Yellowstone, Dillon, Norris,
White Sulphur Springs, and Mcallister. This also includes areas
along the Interstate 90 corridor, from Butte to Bozeman Pass and
Interstate 15, from Dillon to Monida Pass.
</description>
